diagnoses.name: Migraine with aura
diagnoses.description: Migraines with aura are headaches accompanied by sensory disturbances that can include scotoma, scintillation, and parasthesia. Headache usually follows these symptoms.

diagnoses.name: Multiple Sclerosis
diagnoses.description: Multiple sclerosis (MS) is a chronic illness involving your central nervous system (CNS). The immune system attacks myelin, which is the protective layer around nerve fibers, causing inflammation and scar tissue. This can lead to symptoms such as dysphagia, scotoma, scintillation, parasthesia, and headache.

diagnoses.name: Transient Ischemic Attack
diagnoses.description: A transient ischemic attack (TIA), often called a 'mini-stroke', is a temporary period of symptoms similar to those of a stroke. It can cause headache, parasthesia, and sometimes dysphagia. Unlike a stroke, the symptoms of a TIA are temporary and usually resolve within 24 hours.

diagnoses.name: Brain Tumor
diagnoses.description: Brain tumors can cause a variety of symptoms depending on their location. Symptoms can include headache, dysphagia (if the tumor affects areas of the brain responsible for swallowing), scotoma, scintillation, and parasthesia.

diagnoses.name: Myasthenia Gravis
diagnoses.description: Myasthenia gravis is a chronic autoimmune, neuromuscular disease that causes weakness in the skeletal muscles, which are responsible for breathing and moving parts of the body, including the arms and legs. It can lead to dysphagia and possibly contribute to headache.

diagnoses.name: Stroke
diagnoses.description: A stroke occurs when the blood supply to part of your brain is interrupted or reduced, preventing brain tissue from getting oxygen and nutrients. Brain cells begin to die in minutes. Symptoms can include headache, dysphagia, scintillation, scotoma, and parasthesia.

diagnoses.name: Migrainous Infarction
diagnoses.description: A migrainous infarction is a rare form of ischemic stroke occurring during a migraine with aura attack. Symptoms include those typical of a migraine with aura, such as scintillation and scotoma, and can also include parasthesia and headache.

diagnoses.name: Optic Neuritis
diagnoses.description: Optic neuritis is inflammation that damages the optic nerve, a bundle of nerve fibers that transmits visual information from your eye to your brain. Pain and temporary vision loss in one eye are common symptoms, along with scotoma and sometimes headaches.

diagnoses.name: Arnold-Chiari Malformation
diagnoses.description: Arnold-Chiari malformation is a condition in which brain tissue extends into the spinal canal. It occurs when part of your skull is abnormally small or misshapen, pressing on your brain and forcing it downward. Symptoms can include headache, dysphagia, and sometimes parasthesia.

diagnoses.name: Temporal Arteritis
diagnoses.description: Temporal arteritis is an inflammation of blood vessels, commonly in the head, that can cause headache, vision problems, and jaw pain. Scotoma and other visual disturbances may occur, and in severe cases, it can lead to complications such as stroke.
